Setting up virtual environment. 
1. Installing the library
  ```
  run command to install virtual environment  pip install virtualenv
  ```

2. Setup virtual environment for project
  ```
  pyvenv-3.4 /path/to/virtualenv
  ```

Installing dependencies
```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Switching into virtual environment
```
source /path/to/virtualenv/bin/activate
```

Running console 
```
python manage.py shell
```

Running migration
```
python manage.py 
```

